"title": "5688: firstborn",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5688",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The firstborn male in a family; as in many cultures, in an Israelite family the eldest son had unique privileges, including the right of inheritance. The title “firstborn” was therefore a title of honour.</p>\n<h2>The privileges of the firstborn</h2>\n<h3>The place of honour in the family</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen10:15\">GEN 10:15</a></strong> <em>In this and other lists, the firstborn is specially noted</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen43:33\">GEN 43:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:21\">GEN 22:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:13\">GEN 25:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:23\">GEN 35:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen36:15\">GEN 36:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:8\">GEN 46:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:17\">DEU 33:17</a></p>\n<h3>The right of inheritance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:15-Deut21:17\">DEU 21:15–21:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr21:3\">2CH 21:3</a></p>\n<h3>The right to a blessing</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:19\">GEN 27:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:30-Gen27:39\">GEN 27:30–27:39</a></p>\n<h3>The sin of despising these privileges</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:31-Gen25:34\">GEN 25:31–25:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:16-Heb12:17\">HEB 12:16–12:17</a></p>\n<h3>These privileges could be transferred</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen48:14\">GEN 48:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen48:18-Gen48:19\">GEN 48:18–48:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:3-Gen49:4\">GEN 49:3–49:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr2:3\">1CH 2:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr5:1-1Chr5:2\">1CH 5:1–5:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr26:10\">1CH 26:10</a></p>\n<h2>The death of the firstborn a great tragedy</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:23\">EXO 4:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod11:4-Exod11:6\">EXO 11:4–11:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:12\">EXO 12:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:29\">EXO 12:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num33:4\">NUM 33:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:26\">JOS 6:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs16:34\">1KI 16:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:51\">PSA 78:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:36\">PSA 105:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps135:8\">PSA 135:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps136:10\">PSA 136:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:28\">HEB 11:28</a></p>\n<h3>Repentance likened to grief over the death of a firstborn</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech12:10\">ZEC 12:10</a></p>\n<h2>God's claim upon the firstborn</h2>\n<h3>In ancient times</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:4\">GEN 4:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:1-Gen22:2\">GEN 22:1–22:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:12\">GEN 22:12</a></p>\n<h3>After the exodus</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:1-Exod13:2\">EXO 13:1–13:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:11-Exod13:15\">EXO 13:11–13:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:29\">EXO 22:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:19-Exod34:20\">EXO 34:19–34:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:15\">NUM 18:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:17\">NUM 18:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:23\">DEU 14:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:19\">DEU 15:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:36\">NEH 10:36</a></p>\n<h3>The Levites consecrated in place of the firstborn</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num3:11-Num3:13\">NUM 3:11–3:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num3:39-Num3:51\">NUM 3:39–3:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num8:15-Num8:18\">NUM 8:15–8:18</a></p>\n<h3>The offering of a firstborn insufficient to redeem from the consequences of sin</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:7\">MIC 6:7</a></p>\n<h2>Heathen sacrifice of the firstborn</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr28:3\">2CH 28:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:26\">EZK 20:26</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ the ``firstborn''</h2>\n<h3>The firstborn of Mary</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:7\">LUK 2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:22-Luke2:23\">LUK 2:22–2:23</a></p>\n<h3>The firstborn of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:29\">ROM 8:29</a></strong> <em>“firstborn” here means that Jesus Christ is above creation, rather than part of it. The title “firstborn” has strong Messianic associations</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:15\">COL 1:15</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:6\">HEB 1:6</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The ``firstborn from the dead''</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:18\">COL 1:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:5\">REV 1:5</a></p>\n<h2>God's people honoured as his ``firstborn''</h2>\n<h3>Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:22\">EXO 4:22</a></strong></p>\n<h3>David</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:27\">PSA 89:27</a> <em>prophetic of Jesus Christ</em></p>\n<h3>Ephraim</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:9\">JER 31:9</a></p>\n<h3>The church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:23\">HEB 12:23</a></strong></p>",
